                                    "btc-halving-disclaimer-desc-4": "Please also note that data relating to the above-mentioned cryptocurrency presented here (such as its current live price) are based on third party sources. They are presented to you on an “as is” basis and for informational purposes only, without representation or warranty of any kind. Links provided to third-party sites are also not under Binance’s control. Binance is not responsible for the reliability and accuracy of such third-party sites and their contents.",
                                    "btc-halving-disclaimer-title": "Disclaimer",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a1": "Bitcoin halving is a prescheduled event where the reward for mining and verifying new blocks is reduced by 50% and miners earn only half the number of BTC per mined block. Scheduled to take place every 210,000 blocks, or approximately every four years, Bitcoin halvings continue until the network has produced the maximum total supply of 21 million BTC.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a2": "When Bitcoin halves, the reward for mining a new block is cut in half. This reduces the rate at which new BTC are created, effectively lowering the inflation rate of the cryptocurrency. The halving event occurs approximately every four years and is part of Bitcoin's controlled supply, aiming to limit the total number of BTC to 21 million.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a3": "The Bitcoin mining algorithm has a target block time of approximately 10 minutes. However, the actual time can vary, with some blocks taking more or less than 10 minutes to mine. This variation can affect the time frame to reach the next halving, which is expected to take place in April 2024.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a4": "Bitcoin halving events draw attention to the cryptocurrency market, including Altcoins. Investors may become more optimistic about the potential price growth of other cryptocurrencies. This excitement can lead to increased investment in Altcoins, causing their prices to rise. Additionally, some miners may switch to mine Altcoins that offer better rewards as Bitcoin's mining reward decreases.\u2028            ",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a5": "Dollar Cost Averaging (DCA) is an investment strategy that involves regularly investing a fixed amount of money in an asset over a period of time, regardless of market conditions. This approach helps investors reduce the impact of market volatility and the risks associated with trying to time the market.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a6-1": "Auto-Invest allows you to automate crypto investments and grow your crypto holdings. It is a dollar-cost averaging (DCA) strategy. You can choose the cryptocurrencies you want to purchase on a regular basis.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a6-2": "You can choose to create a [Single Token] plan for a single cryptocurrency, or create a [Portfolio] plan to buy multiple cryptocurrencies in one portfolio. Additionally, you can create an [Index-Linked plan] if the service is offered to you in your local jurisdictions. You can find out more below in the response to 'What is the Auto-Invest Index-Linked Plan?'",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a6-3": "In some jurisdictions, your purchased BNB will be automatically deposited into BNB Vault, and the other crypto purchased will be deposited to your Simple Earn Flexible Products account, so you can grow your crypto holdings.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a7": "220+ cryptocurrencies and 20+ payment options are supported. For the full set of cryptocurrencies, stablecoins, and fiat currencies supported, explore our products or visit our official FAQ.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a8-1": "Step 1 - Choose the crypto you want to buy or a [Multi Asset] purchase.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a8-2": "Step 2 - Choose how much you want to buy and select your preferred payment method - stablecoins, fiat currencies or cryptos that are allowed for subscriptions.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a8-3": "Step 3 - Select a payment order. You can also choose to enable the [Simple Earn Wallet] option. Once enabled, if your Spot Wallet balance is insufficient, the system will automatically redeem the assets from your balance in Simple Earn Flexible Products to complete the purchase.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a8-4": "Step 4 - Select a recurring cycle for how often you want to buy crypto. Alternatively, you can make a one-time purchase.",
                                    "btc-halving-faq-a8-5": "Step 5 - Invest",
